{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/pyelonephritis-acute/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"5d08cf27-dc02-5eea-b5c3-b6308f0d1374","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 8b8c2b53-35e4-45c2-bd00-a7f2018978a2 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 8b8c2b53-35e4-45c2-bd00-a7f2018978a2 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 57b4d9d4-3054-4a92-bb04-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field fcc7c7d6-c4cd-46df-a730-a7f2018978a2 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field fcc7c7d6-c4cd-46df-a730-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- begin field 234bf416-de1d-4b8b-b71d-a7f2018978a2 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 234bf416-de1d-4b8b-b71d-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- begin field 019f0d99-693d-4eff-80b3-a7f2018978a2 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 019f0d99-693d-4eff-80b3-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- begin field 315f7158-3a45-4ea6-be2d-a7f2018978a2 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 315f7158-3a45-4ea6-be2d-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- begin field 0dcc11f3-e1f0-422c-b1d0-a7f2018978a2 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 0dcc11f3-e1f0-422c-b1d0-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- begin field d54f73fe-3971-436a-a283-a7f2018978a2 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field d54f73fe-3971-436a-a283-a7f2018978a2 --><!-- end item 57b4d9d4-3054-4a92-bb04-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"1ee909c1-6785-5b3a-a71f-c675db878f51","topicId":"44207967-66bd-4750-aa84-8d9a53c85df0","topicName":"Pyelonephritis - acute","slug":"pyelonephritis-acute","lastRevised":"Last revised in November 2020","chapters":[{"id":"02ed8486-e946-512b-82a2-668a9ff16030","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"46426ef8-dbce-5314-8014-895736033f59","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e0c98a4b-654e-5b3d-acbe-7af83e06b09e","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"d957e39c-6b0e-5ab2-b109-25b3d89f2a69","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"ac7d383b-749f-5a71-b1a3-64b8ee85c6e4","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"d8333a3b-c658-5cb9-8d52-f4731cb7591a","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"82a178c6-fb1b-55a0-8fff-db47a9a4e56f","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"528ddc23-f69e-558e-a643-3efdf3ed0c46","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"251eeb06-8579-5cc4-8e1a-95f1d66519b7","slug":"audit-criteria","full